25/04/2007
WASHINGTON, United States -- President George W. Bush will visit Albania and Bulgaria during an upcoming European trip, the White House announced on Tuesday (April 24th). The focus of the weeklong tour will be the G8 Summit in seaside Heiligendamm, Germany, in early June. Bush will then travel to the Vatican for his first meeting with Pope Benedict XVI and will spend a day in Rome talking with top Italian officials. He will then travel to Tirana on June 10th and to Sofia the next day. (Sega, Trud - 25/04/07; Reuters, DPA, Mediapool, Top-Channel, RFE, VOA, 24-ore - 24/04/07)
